desc=Halflings are small, slightly stocky folk who stand around three feet tall and weigh around 60 pounds. They have curly brown hair on their heads and feet, but rarely have facial hair. They are usually fair-skinned, often with ruddy cheeks. Halflings are remarkably rugged for their small size. They are dexterous and nimble, capable of moving quietly and remaining very still. They usually go barefoot. Halflings are typically outgoing, unassuming and good-natured. They live about a hundred years.//Halflings are unusually accurate with all sorts of ranged weapons, gaining a bonus to accuracy, and also a bonus to initiative die rolls, due to their quick wit and reactions.//In their preferred forest terrain, they are able to hide very effectively, with a 90 percent chance of success. Even indoors, in dungeons or in non-preferred terrain, any halfling can `!hide` with 70 percent effectiveness, regardless of class.//Being a small race, Halflings cannot wield Large weapons at all (Greataxe, Longbow, Heavy Crossbow, Greatsword, Maul, Quarterstaff, Polearm) and must use Medium weapons with two hands, even if they can be used with one hand normally (Battleaxe, Shortbow, Light Crossbow, Longsword/Scimitar, Mace, Club/Cudgel/Walking Staff, Spear). 


