desc=Cavemen are a species closely related to Humans; they are shorter and stockier, and much more heavily muscled. They do not all actually live in caves. Whether they are actually less intelligent than "normal" humans or not is a matter of debate, but it is true that they do not have the facility for language that other human, demi-human, and humanoid races have. However, they do seem to be able to communicate basic information amongst themselves through complex grunts and vocalizations similar to what one might hear from the great apes.//Caveman Clerics and Druids are still able to vocalize their spells despite this language limitation, doing so in peculiar ways that are unrecognizable by other races.//Cavemen are wise in the ways of nature, and make for excellent Druids or Rangers, but they lack the ability to communicate or understand advanced concepts such as arcane spellcasting. Cavemen can 'learn' languages, but only rudimentary concepts are understood.//Cavemen are very attuned to their surroundings, and like Elves are seldom surprised, only being surprised on a 1 instead of a 1-2 on the 1d6 roll.

