desc=Goblins are small, wicked humanoids who favor ambushes, overwhelming odds, dirty tricks, and any other edge they can devise. An adult goblin stands around 3' tall and weighs around 40 pounds. Its eyes are unusually bright and crafty-looking, varying in color from red to yellow. A goblin's skin color ranges from yellow to green to orange to red; usually all members of a single tribe are about the same color. Goblins wear clothing of dark leather.//Crafty and mechanically inclined, a goblin notices secret doors as well as an Elf, and is able to detect slanting passages, traps, shifting walls, and new construction as well as a Dwarf (Noticing traps on a 1-2 on a 1d6). Like most dark-dwelling races, a Goblin has Darkvision out to 60'.//Being a small race, Goblins cannot wield Large weapons at all (Greataxe, Longbow, Heavy Crossbow, Greatsword, Maul, Quarterstaff, Polearm) and must use Medium weapons with two hands, even if they can be used with one hand normally (Battleaxe, Shortbow, Light Crossbow, Longsword/Scimitar, Mace, Club/Cudgel/Walking Staff, Spear).

