desc=Kobolds are small, dog-faced reptilian humanoids. A kobold is 2' tall and weighs about 40 pounds. Kobolds tend to perceive larger races as enemies, and are naturally distrustful when encountered. Regardless, kobolds are cunning foes. They prefer ranged combat, closing only when they can see their foes have been weakened. Whenever they can, kobolds prefer to ambush and set up traps.//A kobold may become any class, excluding the combination classes. Kobolds are masters of trapworks and are otherwise very mechanically inclined. They notice secret doors as well as an Elf and traps as well as a Dwarf. Kobolds have Darkvision out to 90'.//Being a small race, Kobolds cannot wield Large weapons at all (Greataxe, Longbow, Heavy Crossbow, Greatsword, Maul, Quarterstaff, Polearm) and must use Medium weapons with two hands, even if they can be used with one hand normally (Battleaxe, Shortbow, Light Crossbow, Longsword/Scimitar, Mace, Club/Cudgel/Walking Staff, Spear).

