desc=A lizard man is uaully 6' to 7' feet tall with green, gray, or brown scales. Its tail is used for balance and is 3' to 4' long. Adult males can weigh from 200 to 250 pounds and are always very strong. Lizardmen are largely indifferent to other races, being primarily interested in their own survival. If aroused, however, they are fearsome warriors, using simple but sound tactics.//Lizard men generally prefer professions associated with nature or survival. Lizardmen have trouble relating to most other races.//Lizardmen are excellent swimmers and can hold their breath for an extended period of time (up to a full turn, or 60 rounds). Lizardmen can bite for 1d6 + Strength modifier in damage, but must forgo any weapon attacks that round. A lizardman fighter can specialize in their own bite.

