desc=Gnomes are small and stocky, moreso than halflings but not as much as dwarves; both male and female gnomes stand around three and a half feet tall and typically weigh around 90 pounds. Their hair and beards may be blond, brown, black, or sometimes red. They have a fair to ruddy complexion. The most noticeable features about a gnome from the standpoint of other races is their pointed ears and noses. They are renowned for their rapidly-changing moods, sometimes gruff and contrary, sometimes whimsical and humorous. They have a lifespan between two and three centuries long.//Gnomes are frail like elves, unable to roll higher than d6 for hit dice regardless of class. They are also small like halflings, unable to wield large weapons and needing to wield medium weapons in two hands. With respect to encumbrance, gnomes are equivalent to halflings.//Gnomes have the ability to see invisible creatures and objects within 30 feet. Such creatures and objects appear as strange magical glows in the shape of the creature or object. A Thief hiding in shadows, an invisible sprite, or a character wearing an elven cloak may all be detected in this way.

