desc=Kenku are a race of disheveled, corvid-like people who hatch from eggs like birds do. They are taller than dwarves, but not taller than a human. They typically come in dark colors, with beaks they can use for loud caws, and sharp talon'd feet that click when they move. Kenku dwell in nests or aeries that are often built near human cities until they reach adulthood, when they set off on their own with bands of like-minded kenkus. They often dwell in human cities, running criminal enterprises and confidence schemes.//A Kenku's wings are disheveled and unusable for flight, though still allowing them to leap great heights with ease, easily clearing 15ft gaps. Their disheveled nature leads their body to being far more frail than other races, with their hitdie size only going up to a d6.//The most noticeable ability of a Kenku is their adept mimicry, allowing them to effortlessly mimic the sounds and voices of other creatures. This ability only copies sounds and voices, and doesn't prevent a creature from figuring out it's a mimicry through other means. Being adept at their own forms of deception, as well as their temperament against that which is holy, Kenku are often paranoid of other creatures they're unfamiliar with, giving them a bonus to their initiative rolls.

[Hopper]
desc=Hopper is the kenku's racial ability that lets it jump higher than normal races. While it doesn't allow for full flight, your disheveled wings do allow you to make 15ft jumps with ease. Wind and other environmental factors may change the distance you can clear with your wings, and how you may use them (Up to GM discretion).

[Mimicry]
desc=Mimicry is the kenku's racial ability that lets them copy the sounds and voices of other creatures effortlessly. This does not prevent a creature from distinguishing it's a mimicry of their voice through what you say, or seeing that you're the one speaking in the voice.

