desc=Tabaxi are a race of cat-like humanoids. There are many rumors regarding their mysterious origin, but in truth they are members of an ancient and reclusive culture commonly found only in the jungles of Hepmonaland. Standing at around five feet tall and weighing around 110 pounds, short fur covers their bodies and they have a non-prehensile tail. The color and pattern of their fur can be that of any domesticated or wild cat. Tabaxi wear clothing, and adventuring tabaxi typically prefer lighter armor. They are quick and graceful, and have excellent eyesight, giving them Darkvision out to 60 feet. They are fiercely curious and sometimes have trouble controlling that impulse. Their average lifespan is about 80 years.//Their feline nature gives them soft paws to silence their movements, and sharp retractable claws that are excellent for clinging to ledges. Their claws are not long enough to cause grievous wounds, and as such may not be used as a natural weapon. Tabaxi can fall up to 20 feet without taking any damage, and any additional fall damage beyond that is halved. Due to their quick nature, tabaxi have improved saves against magic wands and dragon breath.

[Catfall]
desc=Catfall is the tabaxi's natural ability to land on their feet, just like a cat. The first 20 feet of fall damage from any fall are ignored, and any additional fall damage beyond that is halved.


[QuickLearner]
desc=QuickLearner is the racial ability that gives you more experience earned. For humans, it is 10 percent, and for half-elves, half-orcs and half-ogres, it is 5 percent.

[Darkvision]
desc=Darkvision is the ability to see in the dark without the aid of a torch or lantern. Darkvision is experienced in black, white and shades of gray. Different races have different darkvision maximums: half-elves and half-ogres have 30 feet, orcs, half-orcs, dwarves, elves, goblins, hobgoblins, gnolls and bugbears have 60 feet, and kobolds have 90 feet.

[SecretDoor]
desc=SecretDoor is the ability to detect secret doors more effectively. This is handled automatically through the `!door` command, which any character of any race has access to. Having this ability will increase the likelihood that a secret door is found.//Note that full-blooded elves, as well as goblins, hobgoblins and kobolds, can also detect secret doors with but a cursory glance: for elf/goblin/kobold/hobgoblin characters, you may roll `!door` when entering each room, and this does not count as your exploration turn's action.//For other races such as half-elf and those without this ability, you may roll `!door` as your character's action on an exploration turn.

[GhoulImmune]
desc=GhoulImmune is the elven racial ability to ignore the paralyzing effect of a ghoul or ghast's claw attacks. Keep in mind this does not make the elf immune to all paralyzing monster abilities, but it does defend against the spell GhoulishHands.

[Alert]
desc=Alert is the racial ability to be surprised less often. Surprise rolls are called by the GM with the `!surprise` command, and failing one means the monsters get the drop on you - this can often prove fatal.

[Frail]
desc=Frail is a racial "ability" that denotes that your character's race is especially frail, and may not roll higher than a d6 for hit points, regardless of class.

[Large]
desc=Large characters have increased hit die values (which determine HP), as well as +1 on the roll when opening stuck doors or performing other feats of Strength.

[Aim]
desc=Aim is the halfling racial ability which gives them greater accuracy, gaining a +1 to all attack rolls with ranged weapons.

[QuickWit]
desc=QuickWit is the halfling racial ability to react quickly to any danger, giving them a +1 on initiative rolls.

[ForestStealth]
desc=ForestStealth is the halfling racial ability that gives them automatic 90 percent success when hiding in any forest environment.

[Hide]
desc=Even when not hiding in a forest environment, a halfling gets an automatic 70 percent success with `!s hide`, the thief's "hide in shadows" ability, even if the halfling is not a thief or other class capable of using the hide skill!

[Small]
desc=Small races have lower carry weight thresholds (they get into 'heavy' weight and slower move speed more easily), as well as equipment restrictions. A small character must hold a longsword, mace, or battleaxe in two hands, and may not wield a greatsword, greataxe, maul, polearm, longbow, heavy crossbow, or quarterstaff. As such, the 'small' weapons such as warhammer, shortsword, handaxe and sling are ideal for small characters.

[ReactPlus]
desc=ReactPlus is the half-orc's racial ability to be received more amicably by others, whether monsters or men. Half-orcs make for natural diplomats as a result, very much unlike their full-blooded brethren.

[Scent]
desc=Scent is the gnoll's racial ability to detect hidden or invisible creatures with supernatural scent. This does not give the gnoll ability to see invisible creatures, and as such they will still have a -2 to attack rolls against them.

[Stonecunning]
desc=Stonecunning is the racial ability to detect slanting passages, shifting walls, new construction, and most importantly traps. This is handled automatically in the `!trap` command, which any race has access to regardless of having this ability. Having Stonecunning makes your character's race more effective at `!trap`, though there are other ways to increase this further, such as playing a Scout or Thief.

[Swim]
desc=Swim gives lizardmen a swim speed, as well as lets them hold their breath for a full turn (60 rounds) under water. Keep in mind wearing metal armor or carrying too much weight can still lead to drowning.

[Bite]
desc=Bite is the lizardman's racial ability to attack with a bite. Doing so is simple: `!a bite (target)` example: `!a bite go1`. Bites deal 1d6 + strength modifier in piercing damage. A lizardman fighter may specialize in their bite with `!spec bite`.

[SeeInvisible]
desc=SeeInvisible is the gnome's racial ability to naturally see any invisible creatures or objects within 30 feet. Such creatures and objects appear as strange magical glows in the shape of the creature or object. A Thief hiding in shadows, an invisible sprite, or a character wearing an elven cloak may all be detected in this way.
